name: Thane of East County
description: A backstage romance leads a pair of actors down a dark path, as they discover their lives beginning to mirror the story of Shakespeare's bloodiest play.

review.author: DanTheButler
review.heading: Keller beat Coen to a black-and-white adaptation of Macbeth
review.reviewBody: One of a few great films out of San Diego, this monochromatic adaptation of Macbeth is soaked in blood. While the story follows its own path, this is a film ahead of its time. Character development, performances and storytelling are far more superior to some of Hollywood's big budgets still being made today. While this film has not hit the radar yet for its target audience, I am curious to see what this team is cooking up next. Shakespeare would be proud.

keywords: neo noir,theater,san diego california,experimental film,supernatural power
